Buffer {
    area: Rect { x: 0, y: 0, width: 80, height: 18 },
    content: [
        "           ┌──────────────────────────Help──────────────────────────┐           ",
        "           │The Hit Manager shows the processes that hit breakpoints│           ",
        "           │and become stopped by tracexec. A process can stop at   │           ",
        "           │syscall-enter(right before exec) or syscall-exit(right  │           ",
        "           │after exec).                                            │           ",
        "           │By default, tracexec uses seccomp-bpf to speed up ptrace│           ",
        "           │operations so that there is minimal overhead when       │           ",
        "           │running programs inside tracexec. However, this comes   │           ",
        "           │with a limitation that detached tracees and their       │           ",
        "           │children will not be able to use execve{,at} syscall.   │           ",
        "           │Usually it is shown as the following error: Function not│           ",
        "           │implemented. To workaround this problem, run tracexec   │           ",
        "           │with --seccomp-bpf=off flag.                            │           ",
        "           │You can detach, resume or detach and launch external    │           ",
        "           │commands for the stopped processes. The {{PID}}         │           ",
        "           │parameter in the external command will be replaced with │           ",
        "           │the PID of the detached and stopped process. For        │           ",
        "           └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘           ",
    ],
